       BUILD_API=2
        WEB_SITE=http://www.logilab.org/vcalsax/
         ENTERED=20020714
         UPDATED=20020714
           SHORT="a simple Python module for managing scheduler data in XML"
cat << EOF
VCalSax is a simple Python module for managing scheduler data in XML.
VCalSax allows to load data from VCalendar files into DOM trees. And to
rewrite such trees as VCalendar files.
For making such conversions, VCalSax defines a Sax parser which changes 
the VCalendar format to a specific XML format, and a XSL Transform to 
build VCalendar files.
Note that VCalendar is a standard format for scheduler data used in 
many calendar software (KOrganizer, Evolution and maybe even Outlook...)
EOF
